Selenium class8

Implicit wait:
Well be applied for findElement method.

Explicit wait or WebDriver Wait:
it used to tell WebDriver to wait for a certain condition before throwing an exception
for specified condition.
before throwing an exception for a specified condition

Explicit wait works with  ExpectedCondition class and wait until certain condition are met or the
given time is achieved.

* sign in xpath is a wild card which can identify any tag-name
Example:
//*[contains(text(), "Syntax")]

Fluent  Wait --> global wait
it is used to tell webDriver to wait to sertn condition as well as it frequency before throwing an expectation

Implicit Wait --> waits to locate the element
Explicits Wait--> wait until certain condition
Fluent wait --> set timeouts,polling and ignore needed exception in the given time

WebTables:

WevTables are element on the webpage  which are constructed by having rows and columns
1.Static webtable(nothing changes)
2.Dynamic webtable(data change inside of your table)

WebTables consist of different sections or parts
<table>
   <thead>
         <tr>
         <th></th>  column data or heading
         </tr>
   </thead>
   <tbody>
          <tr>
          <td></td> --tables data
         </tr>
   </tbody>
</table>

